txt.en: 'Near Seregost, trees get spooky. Sometimes they move! One time, I saw a tree pick up an Orc and smash him into ground! I'm not crazy, right? Better watch out while we're over there.'

You have defeated several frightening Huorns in the Agarnaith wilds. The forces of the west will be a little safer when the conflict with Seregost inevitably occurs. At the very least, you'll know what to look for in the future when you are not quite sure if that tree is moving on its own.
'Near Seregost, trees get spooky. Sometimes they move! One time, I saw a tree pick up an Orc and smash him into ground! I'm not crazy, right? Better watch out while we're over there.'
Gory Huorns can be found in the wilds of Agarnaith, near Seregost.\n\nYou should defeat gory Huorns.
The deeper swamps of Agarnaith are home to some true horrors. One of them is the Huorn, perfectly adapted to Agarnaith's unique trees.
